claim.claim-text:
An adsorption bed (2) for a rapid cycle pressure swing adsorption (RSPSA) device comprising a guard layer (4) at a feed end of the bed, the guard layer (4) comprising a laminate sheet (15) comprising a guard adsorbent, wherein the channel fraction of the guard layer (4) is greater than 50%, the channel fraction being defined as 1 minus the absorbent sheet fraction, the adsorbent sheet fraction being defined as the volume of the laminate sheet divided by the volume of the guard layer;

wherein the surface of the laminate sheet (15) is textured (15A) thereby introducing surface voids (17) to the laminate sheet (15), the surface voids (17) being defined as the volume defined by the peak-to-peak thickness TA of the laminate sheet (15) minus the volume of the envelope of the laminate sheet (15), and

wherein the surface void fraction of the laminate sheet (15) is between about 20 and 50%, the surface void fraction being defined as the volume of the surface voids (17) divided by the sum of the volume of the laminate sheet (15) plus the volume of the surface voids (17).
